[94m[Read][0m [95m/Users/jbogaty/src/arcade-cabinet/grovekeeper/jest.setup.ts[0m
The root cause is `react-native-css-interop`'s JSX runtime being loaded when processing the `.tsx` file. The clean solution is to extract the pure functions to a separate `.ts` file (no JSX):

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- When pure logic is co-located in a `.tsx` file, Jest can't import just the logic without triggering the full JSX runtime chain — `react-native-css-interop` runs `Appearance.getColorScheme()` at module init. Extracting to a plain `.ts` utility file breaks the dependency chain entirely.
- This is the same "testable seam" pattern as `resolveGLBPath` — pure functions live in a `.ts` file, component imports from it, tests import from it directly, bypassing all UI module initialization.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
